<p>NATO on Wednesday launched a new effort dubbed “Arctic Sentry” to coordinate allied military activity in the High North, as the alliance looks to strengthen Arctic security while navigating tensions sparked by President Trump’s push for the United States to acquire Greenland. NATO leaders cast the move as a response to Russia’s increased military activity in the Arctic and China’s growing interest in the region.</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/GpwbV6Tp5ERJkojesVCIq7YENVTg2a1kEEXPajGb5m_JdnaWESq83RXNHlgCEaRcoqO-ceeCleiGEN2CC5zQIVwLnK3Yk3dEJjdtM8yDtpp6oVa5i9JJC-Qj64azFraLMQOZn55YpmmFLmdh8BOuSSquM43tSJYTQGaJCgrKw5OJ4g51J3q-v0OM8Az9IhBbAk8_xA' alt='A Danish navy vessel patrolling the waters off Nuuk, Greenland, in March.' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Coordination focus: NATO’s military headquarters says Arctic Sentry is a framework for coordinating a growing allied military presence in the Arctic.</li><li>No numbers yet: NATO has not put figures on the forces or assets tied to Arctic Sentry. Outlets said it is still unclear whether the effort includes major new deployments.</li><li>Alliance politics: POLITICO reported that some allies view the initiative as mostly symbolic — and designed to keep President Trump “onside” after his January annexation threats unsettled partners.</li><li>Reporting basis: POLITICO said it spoke with 13 NATO diplomats, alliance officials, and military analysts about Arctic Sentry’s motives and scope.</li><li>De-escalation messaging: Deutsche Welle described the mission as an attempt to strengthen Arctic security while also cooling the intra-alliance dispute over Greenland.</li></ul><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>NATO leadership: NATO Secretary-General Mark Rutte said the alliance needs to do more in the High North because Russia has stepped up military activity there and China is showing greater interest. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nato-launches-symbolic-arctic-sentry-mission-to-placate-us-donald-trump-on-greenland/'>POLITICO</a>)</li><li>NATO diplomats and analysts: Some of those cited by POLITICO said the push for Arctic Sentry was driven by U.S. pressure after Trump’s Greenland threats, and that it is reacting to what they see as a largely exaggerated danger. (<a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nato-launches-symbolic-arctic-sentry-mission-to-placate-us-donald-trump-on-greenland/'>POLITICO</a>)</li><li>NATO (military HQ): NATO’s military headquarters described Arctic Sentry as a coordination framework for a stronger allied Arctic presence, pointing to exercises linked to Greenland such as Denmark’s Arctic Endurance. (<a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3343235/nato-launches-arctic-sentry-mission-bid-ease-greenland-tensions-trump'>South China Morning Post</a>)</li><li>Media analysis: The New York Times highlighted Russia’s Arctic military posture as a central driver of NATO’s push to increase its presence in the region. (<a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/11/world/europe/nato-arctic-russia-military.html'>The New York Times</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.politico.eu/article/nato-launches-symbolic-arctic-sentry-mission-to-placate-us-donald-trump-on-greenland/'>NATO deploys to Greenland to keep Trump onside</a> - politico.eu</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/nato-launches-new-arctic-sentry-mission/article70620410.ece'>NATO launches new &#x27;Arctic Sentry&#x27; mission</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.nytimes.com/2026/02/11/world/europe/nato-arctic-russia-military.html'>NATO Is Expected to Step Up Arctic Security. Here’s Why.</a> - nytimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dw.com/en/nato-begins-arctic-sentry-mission-to-secure-region/a-75912376'>NATO begins &#x27;Arctic Sentry&#x27; mission to secure region</a> - dw.com</li><li><a href='https://www.scmp.com/news/world/europe/article/3343235/nato-launches-arctic-sentry-mission-bid-ease-greenland-tensions-trump'>Nato launches Arctic Sentry mission in bid to ease Greenland tensions with Trump</a> - scmp.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/nato-launches-arctic-sentry-as-alliance-looks-to-reset-after-greenland-tensions-13978758.html'>Nato launches &#x27;Arctic Sentry&#x27; as alliance looks to reset after Greenland tensions</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.pbs.org/newshour/world/nato-launches-arctic-sentry-military-effort-in-seeking-to-move-on-from-greenland-dispute'>NATO launches Arctic Sentry military effort in seeking to move on from Greenland dispute</a> - pbs.org</li></ul>